- HEAD and OPTIONS are not explicitly defined in the code, but Flask (Werkzeug) automatically provides appropriate responses for HEAD (when GET is allowed) and OPTIONS for routes. Thus, HEAD and OPTIONS are acceptable by virtue of Flaskâ€™s default behavior.
- POST, PUT, DELETE, PATCH, and TRACE are not defined for this endpoint, so they are not acceptable based on the code. TRACE is typically not implemented by Flask by default.

In short: /cms/admin/users supports GET (and, by Flask behavior, HEAD and OPTIONS), but not POST, PUT, DELETE, PATCH, or TRACE.
